Deputy National Security Advisor Denis McDonough traveled to Afghanistan to follow up on the Afghanistan and Pakistan Annual Review. He met with Afghan National Security Adviser Dr. Rangin Dadfar Spanta and provided him with a readout of the review. McDonough also met with Ambassador Eikenberry, Ambassador Hans Klemm, and the Country Team at the American Embassy in Kabul to discuss development and governance plans, transparency and accountability in U.S. contracting, and Afghan Security Force training. He visited Bagram Air Field and received updates on efforts to clear Taliban strongholds along the border with Pakistan. McDonough also toured the Parwan detention facility, which is being transferred to Afghan control. In Kandahar, he was briefed on ongoing clearing efforts in Taliban strongholds and received briefings on development and stability operations.